                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12830693" author="ryanobjc" created="Sun, 7 Feb 2010 11:07:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;for what it&apos;s worth, my previous testing in 0.20 indicated a single cell can take upwards of 2b ICV calls/day.  The actual contention is fairly low.  We should weigh the implementation complexity against using a sharded counter (which you&apos;d need for multi-DC counters anyways) to achieve truly extreme counter performance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12831040" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 8 Feb 2010 18:52:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Setting this to minor priority and not for 0.21, let&apos;s revisit if we need to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13651397" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 22:45:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably will never happen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
